sub_topic: Identifying the isomorphism between two graphs.
message_1: Consider two graphs A and B, where A has 6 vertices and 9 edges, and B has 6 vertices and 8 edges. Determine whether A and B are isomorphic or not. If they are, provide an isomorphism between the two graphs.
message_2:
To determine if two graphs A and B are isomorphic, we need to check if there exists a one-to-one correspondence between their vertices such that the adjacency between the vertices is preserved.

However, in this case, we can quickly conclude that A and B are not isomorphic because they have a different number of edges. Graph A has 9 edges, while graph B has 8 edges. Since the number of edges is not the same, there cannot be an isomorphism between these two graphs.
